From 53075d24cc96fbfe629c6376e55dd81c57641f53 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: quivent <quivent@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 17:16:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] fix(mtp): end-to-end MTP head load+execute for qwen35 dense
 Qwen3.5-27B
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Addresses the infrastructure gaps that prevented a converted Qwen3.5-27B
(with mtp_num_hidden_layers: 1) from loading and running the MTP draft path.
Every fix in this commit is backed by either a runtime error, a tensor-shape
diff against the working main forward path, or a cross-reference with another
arch that has the correct pattern.

Fix 1 — gguf-py/gguf/constants.py QWEN35 tensor list
  Add FFN_NORM + 6 NEXTN_* entries so the converter's tensor_map accepts the
  remapped MTP tensor names. Strictly additive; no other arch touched.

Fix 2 — convert_hf_to_gguf.py Qwen3NextModel.__init__
  Override __init__ to bump self.block_count by hparams.mtp_num_hidden_layers
  after super().__init__, then rebuild self.tensor_map so the MTP layer at
  index 64 is in range. Gated on n_mtp > 0 so the 80B-A3B MoE path is
  unaffected. Propagates via _LinearAttentionVReorderBase to Qwen3_5TextModel.

Fix 3 — src/llama-model.cpp QWEN35 hparams + loader
  * Read LLM_KV_NEXTN_PREDICT_LAYERS in load_hparams (optional).
  * Fix the recurrent_layer_arr loop so the MTP layer at index n_base is
    never marked recurrent — MTP is always dense full-attention.
  * Extend the type switch to map (n_layer - nextn_predict_layers) == 64 to
    LLM_TYPE_27B.
  * Add a layer.nextn.* allocation block (eh_proj, enorm, hnorm,
    shared_head_norm required; embed_tokens, shared_head_head optional for
    mtp_use_dedicated_embeddings: False).
  * Replace LLM_TENSOR_ATTN_POST_NORM with LLM_TENSOR_FFN_NORM in the
    attn_post_norm create_tensor call: HF post_attention_layernorm is emitted
    as blk.N.ffn_norm.weight by the Llama-family tensor_mapping, and the
    graph builder uses layer.attn_post_norm as the pre-FFN norm. Pre-existing
    upstream bug — the QWEN35 loader had never been exercised against a real
    converted GGUF. Same fix applied to QWEN35MOE.

Fix 4 — src/llama-arch.cpp QWEN35 tensor registration
  * Replace ATTN_POST_NORM with FFN_NORM in the LLM_TENSOR_NAMES list so tn()
    resolves correctly.
  * Add all six NEXTN_* entries so tn() can substitute blk.%d.* for them.
  * Reclassify NEXTN_* entries from LLM_TENSOR_LAYER_OUTPUT to
    LLM_TENSOR_LAYER_REPEATING: the name template is blk.%d.nextn.* so they
    are per-layer, not global output tensors. Pre-existing upstream bug —
    prior arches only loaded these as TENSOR_NOT_REQUIRED so they escaped
    the layer-index sanity check in create_tensor.

Fix 5 — src/models/qwen35.cpp build_mtp_head
  Rewrite the attention block to mirror the working main path:
  * Use build_attn_inp_no_cache() + build_attn() instead of manual K*Q + softmax
    + scale + ggml_repeat_4d. The manual version had two shape bugs — an
    unnecessary 4D reshape of Qcur_full, and an incorrect ggml_repeat_4d call
    that tried to insert a broadcast axis via repeat (which broadcasts, it
    does not insert).
  * Use 3D views of Qcur_full for Qcur and gate, matching the main path.
  * Switch RoPE from ggml_rope_ext to ggml_rope_multi with hparams.rope_sections,
    matching the main path's MRoPE call. Allocate inp_pos_zero as length 4
    (one position per rope section) instead of length 1.
  * Fall back to model.output (or model.tok_embd if tied) when
    layer.nextn.shared_head_head is null — required for
    mtp_use_dedicated_embeddings: False models like Qwen3.5-27B.

Fix 6 — src/llama-context.cpp mtp_graph_compute
  Upload the full inp_pos_zero tensor contents (size-agnostic zero fill)
  instead of a single int32 — the MTP head now allocates inp_pos_zero as
  length 4 for MRoPE.

Known remaining issue: spec decode rollback path hits backend scheduling
errors around recurrent memory position management (find_slot: non-consecutive
token position) during the verify phase. MTP head itself runs end-to-end and
produces plausible drafts. Separate subsystem.
